  "dateModified": "2026-04-28",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-28",
  "description": "An applied study tracing the actual beneficial parties of specific corporate-financial arrangements: who, named individually, financially benefits from MindGeek/Aylo's continued operation; from Colbeck Capital's hybrid-lending into the porn industry; from the Bruinen-ECP transition; from the Russian-organized-crime/Trump-orbit financing chains. Where the school's main analyses describe what the apparatus does, the who-benefits work names the specific people who benefit from particular configurations of the apparatus's operation. The structural concepts (beneficial ownership, nominee structures, offshore concealment, compliance theater) are tools to make the named persons traceable through the legal-jurisdictional apparatus that conceals them.",
  "name": "Who Benefits",
  "publisher": {
